<div id="review_111935845" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/111935845" />
    <a title="Celeste Ng" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/80835-celeste-ng"><img alt="Celeste Ng" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442458318p2/80835.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/111935845?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Celeste Ng" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Celeste Ng" href="/user/show/80835-celeste-ng">Celeste Ng</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80835-celeste-ng?shelf=asian-am-lit">asian-am-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80835-celeste-ng?shelf=debut-novels">debut-novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer111935845" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer143641186101030762">A moving portrayal of one immigrant girl&apos;s struggle to find a place for herself in the United States. A star student at an elite school by day--and a sweatshop worker at night--the narrator relies on her fierce intelligence to find a way out of her situation and make a better life for herself and her mother. <br/><br/>This novel has some parallels with the author&apos;s life, and I admired it for its honesty and bravery. It did a great job, too, at rendering the rhythms of Chinese speech in English--always a t</span>
  <span id="freeText143641186101030762" style="display:none">A moving portrayal of one immigrant girl's struggle to find a place for herself in the United States. A star student at an elite school by day--and a sweatshop worker at night--the narrator relies on her fierce intelligence to find a way out of her situation and make a better life for herself and her mother. <br /><br />This novel has some parallels with the author's life, and I admired it for its honesty and bravery. It did a great job, too, at rendering the rhythms of Chinese speech in English--always a tricky issue for a writer to navigate. </span>
  <a data-text-id="143641186101030762" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


